Show "Natural language random generation test:".

Show "Traditional Syntax:".
Set random_float to call random.
Show "Random float (0-1): " plus random_float.
Set random_int to call randint with 1, 100.
Show "Random integer (1-100): " plus random_int.

Show "Natural Language Syntax:".

Set random_number to generate a random number between 1 and 100.
Show "Core syntax: random number between 1 and 100: " plus random_number.

Set dice_roll to roll a random number from 1 to 6.
Show "Dice roll from 1 to 6: " plus dice_roll.

Set random_val to generate a random value between 10 and 50.
Show "Random value between 10 and 50: " plus random_val.

Set lucky_number to pick a random integer between 100 and 999.
Show "Lucky number between 100 and 999: " plus lucky_number.

Set min_val to 5.
Set max_val to 15.
Set range_random to generate a random number between min_val and max_val.
Show "Range random between variables: " plus range_random.

Set expr_random to roll a random number from min_val times 2 to max_val plus 10.
Show "Expression random: min_val*2 to max_val+10: " plus expr_random.

Show "Natural language random functions are working!".